# docs/ is tracked, EXCEPT superpowers spec/plan working scratch.
# These stay ignored by default (working artifacts). To commit an IMPORTANT
# spec/plan, get user approval then force-add the specific file:
#   git add -f docs/superpowers/specs/<file>.md
# The ignore is the safety net: it keeps drafts out of `git add -A` so only
# deliberately-chosen docs enter history. (Already committed via -f:
# split-K spec + plan, 2026-06-02.)
docs/superpowers/
